IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: offers students from underserved communities the opportunity to gain professional work experience in Dallas top businesses while earning 65% of cost of their education
IRS990.MissionDesc: The Corporate Work Study Program at Cristo Rey Dallas College Prep offers students from underserved communities the opportunity to gain professional work experience in Dallas top businesses while earning 65% of the cost of their education. Combined with a rigorous, college prep curriculum, students graduate ready to succeed in college and life.
IRS990.Desc: The corporation developed and implemented an internship. Specifically, the corporation partnered with 89 local businesses to provide work study jobs for each of Cristo Rey Dallas high school, INC.'s 357 students during the year ended June 30, 2018. Through these efforts, the corporation was able to provide tuition assistance via qualified education assistance plan ("QEAP") in the amount of $1,963,500.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Liabliity for uncertain tax positions under FIN 48(ASC 740)
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: CRD AND CRDAC ARE EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAXES UNDER SECTIONS 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE (THE CODE), AND CWSP IS EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAXES UNDER SECTION 509(A)(3) OF THE CODE. THEREFORE, NO PROVISION HAS BEEN MADE FOR FEDERAL INCOME TAXES IN THE CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. NONE OF THE ENTITIES ARE CLASSIFIED AS A PRIVATE FOUNDATION. GAAP PRESCRIBES A COMPREHENSIVE MODEL FOR THE FINANCIAL STATEMENT RECOGNITION, MEASUREMENT, PRESENTATION, AND DISCLOSURE OF UNCERTAINTY IN TAX POSITIONS TAKEN OR EXPECTED TO BE TAKEN IN INCOME TAX RETURNS. MANAGEMENT BELIEVES THAT IT HAS NOT TAKEN A TAX POSITION THAT, IF CHALLENGED, WOULD HAVE A MATERIAL EFFECT ON THE SCHOOL'S CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. THE SCHOOL IS EXEMPT FROM PROPERTY TAXES AND FROM STATE INCOME TAXES. CRD, CRDAC, AND CWSP ARE REQUIRED TO FILE AN ANNUAL INFORMATION RETURN WITH THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE. THE ENTITIES FILE FORM 990 IN THE UNITED STATES FEDERAL JURISDICTION WITHIN THE UNITED STATES.
